———————————————————————————————–

ggplot2

———————————————————————————————–

ggplot2是非常好的視覺化系統，論論其繪圖品質或使用方法，都與R內建的plot()相差甚遠。並且ggplot2擁有一個淺顯易懂的系統，明確劃分視覺化步驟，容易上手，產出更是R中所有作圖系統中最優雅的一個。ggplot2作者Hadley Wickham，在 「The Layered Grammar of Graphics 」 一書中定義了，定義了grammar of Graphics，建議在開始學習ggplot2前，可先閱讀。


ggplot2 Tutorial

  • DataCamp
  • ggplot2 Tutorial
  • ggplot2 extensions - gallery
  • R for Data Science


grammar of Graphics

    ggplot2 Layers : 
    
        -   In must of case, we just use the first three Layers.

-  manufacturer  制造商
-  model   模具型號
-  displ   排放量(engine displacement, in litres)  
-  year    年份
-  cyl     發動機數量(number of cylinders) 
-  trans   變速器形式(type of transmission)
-  drv     驅動形式(f = front-wheel drive, r = rear wheel drive, 4 = 4wd)
-  cty     每加侖城市行駛距離(city miles per gallon)
-  hwy     每加侖公路行駛距離(highway miles per gallon)
-  fl      燃料(e: ethenol E85, d: diesel, r: regular, p: premium, c: CNG)
-  class   車輛類型


1.2. Creating a ggplot in first layer

# 做出一個框架
test <- ggplot(data = mpg)


1.3. To see the relationship between displ and hwy

    引擎大小(displ)和燃油效率(hwy)之間呈現負向關係
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))


note : 

    請示想，ggplot是一個沒有副作用(No side effect)的函數。也就是說在這個函數中發生的事情，並不會影響到外面的世界(Global Environment)，所有在ggplot中的操作，只會在函數內的世界(Local Environment)運行。也因為我們將mpg讀進了ggplot的Local Environment，在輸入x-axis, y-axis的時候，才能只使用aes(x = displ, y = hwy)，而不是aes(x = mpg$displ, y = mpg$hwy)。


2. Aesthetic mappings for unordered variable


2.1. unordered variable

    將三維的變數，以二維來觀察
# find the outlier
ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
   geom_point(mapping = aes(color = displ > 5 & hwy > 20))


# 將顏色映射在class上
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = class))


# 將將size映射在class上映射在class上
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, size = class))
## Warning: Using size for a discrete variable is not advised.

    許多呈現方式並不適合unordered variable (class) 
    


library(devtools)
## Warning: package 'devtools' was built under R version 3.4.4

x=ggplot(data = mpg) +

# 下圖
z=ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, shape = class))

ggplot2.multiplot(x,z, cols=1)

2.2. ordered variable


# 發動機數量
 ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = cyl))



2.2.1. Size and color work with continuous variables, they just display a gradient.
- Shape does not work with continuous variables.
 ggplot(data = mpg) + 
        geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, size = cty, color = cty, alpha = cty))



2.2.2. It’s not very helpful to use multiple aes in 2 Dimensions variables.
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
        geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy), shape = 21, stroke = 4)


玩玩看

# 在 aes() 的外部控制顏色
test <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy), color = "blue")


3. Geometric objects


# 上圖
x <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

# 中圖
y <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_line(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

# 下圖
z <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy))

ggplot2.multiplot(x,y,z, cols=1)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


# 用linetype改變線條類型
ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, linetype = drv))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


3.1. global mappings

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


3.2. place multiple geoms in the same plot

ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy, color = drv)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(aes(linetype = drv))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(color = class)) + 
  geom_smooth(data = filter(mpg, class == "subcompact"), se = FALSE)
## Warning: package 'bindrcpp' was built under R version 3.4.4
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'


4. Facets


4.1. facet_grid(row ~ column)

ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)


ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_grid(drv ~ cyl)


ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ cty, nrow = 3)


4.2. Exercises

a <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = drv, y = cyl))

b <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_grid(drv ~ .)

ggplot2.multiplot(a,b, cols=1)

c <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +
  facet_grid(. ~ cyl)

d <- ggplot(data = mpg) + 
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) + 
  facet_wrap(~ class, nrow = 2)



ggplot2.multiplot(c,d, cols=1)

f <- ggplot(data = mpg, mapping = aes(x = displ, y = hwy)) +

ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_pointrange(
    mapping = aes(x = cut, y = depth),
    stat = "summary",
    fun.ymin = min,
    fun.ymax = max,
    fun.y = median
  )


6. Statistical Transformations


6.1. Position adjustments

a <- ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, colour = cut))
b <- ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = cut))

ggplot2.multiplot(a,b, cols = 2)


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity))


ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity)) + 
  geom_bar(alpha = 1/5, position = "identity")

ggplot(data = diamonds, mapping = aes(x = cut, colour = clarity)) + 
  geom_bar(fill = NA, position = "identity")


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity), position = "fill")


ggplot(data = diamonds) + 
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = cut, fill = clarity), position = "dodge")
